overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to ensure all acceptance criteria were met and to address
  any missing functionalities. The agent conducted a detailed analysis,
  identifying several critical gaps, including the absence of a tiredness
  severity scale with safety warnings, lack of explicit detection for COMISA and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, missing outbound resource links, and unweighted
  EDS scoring. Following this review, the agent proceeded to implement these
  high-priority features. This involved updating data types, validation schemas,
  and UI components to incorporate the severity scale, adding complex detection
  logic for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome in both the web and PDF
  reports, integrating a dedicated resources section with placeholder links, and
  refining the EDS scoring mechanism to reflect weighted activities. The
  implementation directly addressed the identified shortcomings, enhancing the
  questionnaire's diagnostic capabilities and user guidance.
